# =============================================================================
# uboot.env — RK3588 A/B-virt emulator: default U-Boot environment text (PWU-AB-1)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Source-of-truth DEFAULT values for the A/B U-Boot environment. This is the
# human-readable / version-controlled form; assemble_ab_disk.sh converts it into
# the binary U-Boot env blob (mkenvimage) when an env partition/region is wired,
# OR these same defaults are applied lazily by boot.cmd's `test -n ... || setenv`
# guards on a fresh disk (PWU-AB-1 uses the lazy-default path; the binary env
# blob lands in a later PWU once the slot-flip OTA agent writes the live env).
#
# Format: one `KEY=VALUE` per line, `#` comments + blank lines ignored. This is
# the exact format `mkenvimage -s <size> -o uboot.env.bin uboot.env` consumes.
#
# Variables (see uboot_ab/README.md + boot.cmd for the state machine):
#   BOOT_ORDER         RAUC/Mender slot order; HEAD = slot tried first.
#   bootlimit          attempts before altbootcmd rollback fires (1 = one try).
#   bootcount          current attempt counter (U-Boot inits to 1 on power-on,
#                      increments each reboot while upgrade_available != 0).
#   upgrade_available  1 = update on probation (counter armed); 0 = confirmed
#                      good / no update in flight (counter frozen).
#   altbootcmd         alternate boot action run when bootcount > bootlimit.
#                      Re-sources boot.scr, whose rollback guard swaps BOOT_ORDER.
#
# Doc refs: https://docs.u-boot.org/en/latest/api/bootcount.html
#           https://docs.mender.io/operating-system-updates-yocto-project/board-integration/bootloader-support/u-boot/manual-u-boot-integration
# =============================================================================
BOOT_ORDER=A B
bootlimit=1
bootcount=1
upgrade_available=0
altbootcmd=run bootcmd
